First of all, this was not hard to make like so many reviewers claimed. Not sure what constitutes a lot of prep time, but this certainly did not. I never use lemon pepper, but bought it for this. Now I know why i don't use it. What a horrible taste! It wrecked the entire meal. My husband, who has been a good sport and eaten everything I've made and tries every adventurous thing on menus, spit this chicken out on his plate!! It seemed like it would be nice - all the roulades I've made in the past have been good, but this was just not appealing. It smelled like sweaty socks and had that nasty lemon pepper. If you want a lemony pepper flavor, why not use fresh ground pepper and fresh lemons? The sauce was really good, but the chicken - a waste of ingredients - good bacon, $12/lb parmesean cheese, etc. YUCK!

