Rating: 4
To quote my husband after I made this the first time: "Sensational!" This wonderful tasting recipe does take a bit of time to make and put together, but the great thing is it can be made early in the day (or maybe even the day before) and still taste terrific. I prepare everything ahead of time, including the browning, baking, and sauce-making. Then I refrigerate all and when ready to serve reheat the sauce, slice the chicken, add it to the sauce to warm it up, then serve as directed. I always serve it with mashed potatoes, and wonder what others use to pair it with. Also, I don't change a thing in the recipe, it is so good as is.

