Rating: 4
I made this dish for a baby shower luncheon. Everybody went crazy over it!!!! It was really easy, too. I made the chicken and the sauce the night before (I secured the chicken with string instead of toothpicks, and I added about 1 cup of sauted mushrooms to the sauce). Then about an hour before the shower, I put the chicken back in the oven to heat, put the sauce on the stove to heat, then sliced the chicken, layed the slices out on a heated tray, poured the warm sauce over the chicken, and set it on my buffet table. Not only was it delicous, but it was easy to prepare at the last minute and the presentation was great. I'll definetly make this dish again!!!!!

