This dish was very easy to prepare. The sauce was somewhat bland, so I'd suggest adding some fresh herbs like basil to liven it up, if that's what you'd prefer. Great for dinner parties, the chicken can be prepared in advance and left in the refrigerator until cooking is required - sauce may be prepared in advance and gently reheated. I didn't bother slicing the roulade before serving - too fussy - and the guests didn't seem to care!